  section#about.content-section
    .section-inner.page-contain
      .section-body-full
        h2 About Us
        p.
          Hack for LA is the official Los Angeles chapter of Code for America, a national nonprofit that believes government can work for the people, by the people, in the 21st century. We bring together coders, designers, entrepreneurs, students, government staff, activists, and other civically engaged individuals to solve the LA region’s biggest civic challenges.
        p.
          Are you press and want to get in touch? Are you interested in becoming a sponsor? Want to just check us out on Slack? Looking to volunteer?
        a(href='#').btn.btn-primary Contact us

